---
// Code Examples Section: Show 3 example commands with syntax highlighting
---

<section class="code-examples py-20 sm:py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-green-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">
        Usage <span class="neon-text">Examples</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Simple commands, powerful results. Copy and paste to get started.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Examples Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <!-- Example 1: Google URL -->
      <div class="example-card">
        <div class="example-header">
          <span class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-500">Example 1</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-400">Generate QR for URL</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="example-code"><code><span class="keyword">cargo run</span> <span class="flag">--</span> <span class="flag">--text</span> <span class="string">"https://google.com"</span> <span class="flag">--output</span> <span class="string">qr.png</span></code></pre>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">Generates a QR code linking to Google and saves it as PNG</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 2: Plain Text -->
      <div class="example-card">
        <div class="example-header">
          <span class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-500">Example 2</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-400">Generate QR for Text</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="example-code"><code><span class="keyword">cargo run</span> <span class="flag">--</span> <span class="flag">--text</span> <span class="string">"Hello World"</span> <span class="flag">--output</span> <span class="string">hello.svg</span></code></pre>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">Creates a scalable SVG QR code with your custom text</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 3: WhatsApp -->
      <div class="example-card lg:col-span-2">
        <div class="example-header">
          <span class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-500">Example 3</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-400">Generate QR for WhatsApp</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="example-code"><code><span class="keyword">cargo run</span> <span class="flag">--</span> <span class="flag">--text</span> <span class="string">"https://wa.me/919876543210"</span> <span class="flag">--output</span> <span class="string">wa.png</span></code></pre>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">Share your WhatsApp contact via QR code - perfect for business cards and social media</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Additional Info -->
    <div class="mt-16 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-500/5 to-transparent border-l-4 border-green-500/50 p-6 rounded">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 text-green-400">💡 Pro Tip</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400">
        You can use QR Generator with any text or URL. Combine it with your shell scripts for automated QR code generation in CI/CD pipelines or batch processing workflows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .example-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(15, 15, 15, 0.8), rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5));
    border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .example-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.5);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .example-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
  }

  .example-code {
    background-color: #0f0f0f;
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .example-code code {
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    color: #d1d5db;
  }

  .keyword {
    color: #22C55E;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .flag {
    color: #60a5fa;
  }

  .string {
    color: #fbbf24;
  }

  .example-code::-webkit-scrollbar {
    height: 4px;
  }

  .example-code::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
    background: #0f0f0f;
  }

  .example-code::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    background: #22C55E;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
</style>
